Her debut novel, Behold the Dreamers, was a finalist for the 2016 PEN/Faulkner Award for Fiction, the 2016 PEN/Robert W. It was also named a best book of 2016 by The Washington Post, NPR, The Boston Globe, The Economist, and The New York Times.

## Early life

Kiara Advani was born on 31 July 1992 in Mumbai, Maharashtra, India. She is the daughter of Jagdeep Advani, a businessman, and Alka Advani, a homemaker. She has a younger brother named Mishaal. She is of Gujarati descent. She attended Jamnabai Narsee School in Mumbai. She then went to the United World College of South East Asia in Singapore. She graduated from the University of Mumbai with a degree in Economics.

## Early life

Idris Elba was born in London, England, on September 6, 1972. He is the son of Winston and Eve Elba. His father is from Sierra Leone, and his mother is from Ghana. He has a brother named Yusuf.
